=================================================================================================================================================

    int i = 1; â†’ We start counting from 1.

    while (i <= 5) â†’ As long as i is less than or equal to 5, the loop keeps running.

    System.out.println("Number: " + i); â†’ It prints the current value of i.

    i = i + 1; â†’ We increase i by 1 in each step so the loop doesn't go forever.
